data.name: Spicy Honey Garlic Shrimp with Broccoli
data.quickTastyDescription: A vibrant dish featuring succulent shrimp tossed in a sweet and slightly spicy honey garlic sauce, served with crunchy broccoli.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.
Add minced garlic and ginger, saut√©ing until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
Add the shrimp to the skillet and cook until pink, approximately 2-3 minutes each side.
In a small bowl, mix honey and soy sauce together. Pour the mixture over the shrimp.
Add broccoli to the skillet and stir to combine, cooking for another 5 minutes until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds and garnish with chopped green onions before serving.
